ler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/Untitled-1-2.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/Untitled-1-2.jpg"><media:title>WBB 2026 Selection Show NCAA</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/Untitled-1-2.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 22:06:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58871</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia to Host NCAA Tournament First and Second Rounds</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/womens-basketball-west-virginia-to-host-ncaa-tournament-first-and-second-rounds</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/14/womens-basketball-west-virginia-to-host-ncaa-tournament-first-and-second-rounds</guid><category>Women's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="we're hosting 1920x1080" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University women's basketball team is set to host the First and Second Rounds of the 2026 NCAA Women's Basketball Tournament, as announced by the NCAA on Saturday afternoon.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png"><media:title>we're hosting 1920x1080</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/14/WBB_HOSTINGSITE_1920x1080.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 15:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>9</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58863</s:story_id></item><item><title>Yehl, Mountaineers Shut Out Baylor to Take Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/15/baseball-yehl-mountaineers-shut-out-baylor-to-take-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/15/baseball-yehl-mountaineers-shut-out-baylor-to-take-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/15/ENX09847.jpeg" /><br /><br />WACO, Texas – A dominant performance on the mound from redshirt junior Maxx Yehl paved the way for an 8-0 victory for the West Virginia University baseball team over Baylor, Sunday afternoon at Baylor Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 13-4 overall and 2-1 in the Big 12 while the Bears fall to 11-8 and 1-2 in conference play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/ENX09847.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/ENX09847.jpeg"><media:title>Maxx Yehl</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/15/ENX09847.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 16:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58868</s:story_id></item><item><title>Wilson’s Final Round 64 Leads WVU to a Third-Place Finish</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/15/golf-wilsons-final-round-64-leads-wvu-to-a-third-place-finish</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/15/golf-wilsons-final-round-64-leads-wvu-to-a-third-place-finish</guid><category>Golf</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Nemacolin Collegiate Invitational action" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2025/9/30/4_GOLF_ACTION_pxwnd.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – For the second round in a row, a West Virginia University golfer shot an 8-under-par 64 at the Schenkel Invitational. This time, it was senior Kaleb Wilson who did so to finish third and to lead the Mountaineers to their best-ever finish at the Schenkel Invitational on Sunday in Statesboro, Georgia.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2025/9/30/4_GOLF_ACTION_pxwnd.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/9/30/4_GOLF_ACTION_pxwnd.jpg"><media:title>Nemacolin Collegiate Invitational action</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/9/30/4_GOLF_ACTION_pxwnd.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 16:45:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>5</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58869</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>